  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Using Technology to Serve Children Who are Deaf</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">It is possible for a child who is deaf or hard of hearing to develop listening and spoken language. Listen and Talk&apos;s early intervention providers coach parents in their home to help their child learn to listen and, in turn, learn to talk. Listen and Talk implemented Virtual Home Visits (VHV) to enable providers to apply their expertise to families more efficiently while maintaining effectiveness. The expansion of the VHV model enables more families to be served across a wider geographical area.</narrative>
  </description>
